<subSubSection id="C3216524FFDBFFA6FF43FA8AFD1CF9FF" pageId="2" pageNumber="182" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8436AFFFDBFFA6FF43FA8AFD1CF9FF" blockId="2.[136,1452,1307,1550]" pageId="2" pageNumber="182">
Schumann’s protologue mentions the label data of a specimen collected by 
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFDBFFA6FC04FA8AFB8FFAC4" box="[975,1092,1307,1333]" pageId="2" pageNumber="182">Luschnath</collectorName>
and preserved in the Herbarium Berolinense (B). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDBFFA6FE80FAAEFE2CFAAB" author="Cunha, M. C. S." box="[331,487,1343,1370]" pageId="2" pageNumber="182" pagination="5 - 41" refId="ref7419" refString="Cunha, M. C. S. (1985) Revisao das especies do genero Luehea Willd. (Tiliaceae), ocorrentes no estado do Rio de Janeiro. Sellowia, Anais Botanicos do Herbario Barbosa Rodrigues 37: 5 - 41." type="journal article" year="1985">
<collectingCountry id="F32C763FFFDBFFA6FE80FAAEFE5FFAA8" box="[331,404,1343,1369]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="2" pageNumber="182">Cunha</collectingCountry>
(1985)
</bibRefCitation>
accepted the specimen 
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDBFFA6FD3DFAAEFC51FAA8" box="[758,922,1343,1369]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="182">Luschnath s.n.</emphasis>
(B) as the 
<typeStatus id="5480880DFFDBFFA6FBD1FAAEFBB7FAA8" box="[1050,1148,1343,1369]" pageId="2" pageNumber="182">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDBFFA6FB6FFAD1FAD2FAA8" authorityName="Schumann" authorityYear="1886" box="[1188,1305,1343,1369]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="2" pageNumber="182" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eichleri">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDBFFA6FB6FFAD1FAD2FAA8" box="[1188,1305,1343,1369]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="182">L. eichleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(“ 
<typeStatus id="5480880DFFDBFFA6FAF9FAAEFA60FAA8" box="[1330,1451,1343,1369]" pageId="2" pageNumber="182">Holotypus</typeStatus>
– B, non vidi”), presumably was not aware that the specimen was destroyed during the Second World War (
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFDBFFA6FA85FAF5FA6CFA8F" box="[1358,1447,1380,1406]" pageId="2" pageNumber="182">R. Vogt</collectorName>
, pers. comm.). With the presence of two duplicates in BR, in accordance with Art. 9.3 of the ICN, we designate herein the specimen (BR0000005491346) as the 
<typeStatus id="5480880DFFDBFFA6FDA0FA3AFD19FA34" box="[619,722,1451,1477]" pageId="2" pageNumber="182">lectotype</typeStatus>
by choosing the best-preserved and completed specimen. 
<location id="8EE46074FFDBFFA6FABBFA3AFA60FA34" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:039287B9FFDBFFA6FF43FB1EFD1CF9FF:8EE46074FFDBFFA6FABBFA3AFA60FA34" box="[1392,1451,1451,1477]" country="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" name="After" pageId="2" pageNumber="182">After</location>
having studied the type materials, the application of the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDBFFA6FC89FA41FC7DFA18" authorityName="Schumann" authorityYear="1886" box="[834,950,1487,1513]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="2" pageNumber="182" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eichleri">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDBFFA6FC89FA41FC7DFA18" box="[834,950,1487,1513]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="182">L. eichleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confirmed as a heterotypic synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDBFFA6FA5EFA41FECBF9FC" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="2" pageNumber="182" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conwentzii">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDBFFA6FA5EFA41FECBF9FC" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="182">L. conwentzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as previously accepted by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDBFFA6FDFEFA62FDB5F9FC" author="Cunha, M. C. S." box="[565,638,1523,1549]" pageId="2" pageNumber="182" pagination="5 - 41" refId="ref7419" refString="Cunha, M. C. S. (1985) Revisao das especies do genero Luehea Willd. (Tiliaceae), ocorrentes no estado do Rio de Janeiro. Sellowia, Anais Botanicos do Herbario Barbosa Rodrigues 37: 5 - 41." type="journal article" year="1985">
<collectingCountry id="F32C763FFFDBFFA6FDFEFA62FDB5F9FC" box="[565,638,1523,1549]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="2" pageNumber="182">Cunha</collectingCountry>
</bibRefCitation>
(1985).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
